Women's Concert Tours Data Cleaning Project
Project Overview

This project demonstrates a complete data-cleaning workflow using Python and Pandas. The dataset contains information about the highest-grossing concert tours by female artists, including tour rankings, gross revenue, number of shows, and tour dates.

The goal of this project was to identify and correct common data quality issues before analysis.

Dataset

The dataset includes:

Artist name
Tour title
Tour rankings
Actual gross revenue
Inflation-adjusted gross revenue
Number of shows
Tour years

The original dataset contained several data-quality issues, including:

Wikipedia citation references ([1], [a], etc.)
Special characters (†, ‡, *)
Currency values stored as text
Missing values
Mixed data types
Year ranges stored in a single column
Cleaning Steps Performed

1. Initial Data Inspection
Examined dataset structure
Identified missing values
Checked for duplicate records

2. Standardized Column Names
Removed hidden whitespace characters
Renamed columns for consistency and readability

3. Removed Wikipedia Artifacts
Removed citation references
Removed special symbols and footnote markers
Cleaned tour title text

4. Converted Data Types
Converted revenue columns from text to numeric values
Converted ranking columns to numeric format

5. Handled Missing Values
Preserved missing ranking information as NaN
Removed the reference column used only for source citations

6. Feature Engineering
Split the Year(s) column into:
Start Year
End Year

7. Validation
Verified data types
Checked remaining missing values
Validated average gross calculations
